  "texts": [
    "Recall that these terms can be thought of as describing the mean field generated by the particles in the system due to their Coulomb interactions.",
    "However, the total energy only counts the interaction between each pair of particles once, and so the 1 2 is needed to prevent double-counting.In the initialization step, we choose some initial trial state P 0 (we will discuss this choice in Sec. 3.2.3).",
    "Denoting the number of electrons as N e and the number of orbitals as N, the k-th iteration step (k ≥ 0) consists of the following sub-tasks:(1) Construct the mean-field Hamiltonian from the current state P k, i.e.H k ≡ H HF [P k].",
    "(2) Diagonalize H k, i.e.",
    "find eigenvalues ϵ i and eigenvectors ψ i,a that satisfy b [H k] ab ψ i,b = ϵ i ψ i,a for 1 ≤ i ≤ N, where we assume that the eigenvalues are ordered such that ϵ i ≤ ϵ i+1."
